{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865036436,"sessionID":"ses_2863226e8ffepDL9AgHZo0O2a1","part":{"id":"prt_d79cdfa23001zRc26XKHpX9VF7","messageID":"msg_d79cde6d0001N1eKgdaxhhCCIk","sessionID":"ses_2863226e8ffepDL9AgHZo0O2a1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a08631444beb4c46b49faf36","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-020\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n25: \n26: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n31: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n32: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n33: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n38: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n39: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n40: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n45: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n46: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n51: - **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n57: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n63: \n64: The system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n69: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n71: - **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n76: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n78: - **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n83: - **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n85:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n86:   - `port`: `8080`\n87:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n88:   - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n93: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n95:   - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n96:   - `--language` overrides `language`\n97:   - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n98:   - `--port` overrides `port`\n99:   - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n100:   - `--description` overrides `description`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n105: \n106: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n111: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n113: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n118: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n120: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n125: - **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n127: - **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n132: \n133: The system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n138: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n139: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n144: - **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n145: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n150: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n156: \n157: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n162: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n163: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n168: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n174: - **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n180: \n181: The system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n186: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n187:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n188:   - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n189:   - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n190:   - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n191:   - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n192:   - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n193:   - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n194:   - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n195:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n200: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n201: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n202: - **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n207: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n208: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n209: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n214: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n215: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n216: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n221: \n222: The system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n225: \n226: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n227: - **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n228: - **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n233: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n234: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n239: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n240: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n245: \n246: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n251: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n252: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n253: - **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n258: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n260: - **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Acceptance Criteria\n265: \n266: - [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n267: - [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n268: - [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n269: - [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n270: - [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n271: - [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n272: - [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n273: - [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n274: - [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n275: - [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Architecture Notes\n280: \n281: ### Key Components\n282: \n283: | Component | Path | Description |\n284: |-----------|------|-------------|\n285: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n286: | PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n287: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n288: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n289: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n290: \n291: ### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n292: \n293: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n294: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n295: | agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n296: | language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n297: | entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n298: | port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n299: | build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n300: | description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n301: | requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n302: \n303: ### CLI Options Mapping\n304: \n305: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n306: |------------|----------------|------|\n307: | `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n308: | `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n309: | `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n310: | `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n311: | `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n312: | `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n313: | `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## References\n318: \n319: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n320: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n321: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n322: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n323: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n324: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775865036410,"end":1775865036433}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865036450,"sessionID":"ses_2863226e8ffepDL9AgHZo0O2a1","part":{"id":"prt_d79cdf538001qvcII0Fmo7OEdc","messageID":"msg_d79cde6d0001N1eKgdaxhhCCIk","sessionID":"ses_2863226e8ffepDL9AgHZo0O2a1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9ab8318d1aed4fb098019324","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/docker_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/docker_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Docker service for AgentCube - handles Dockerfile generation and Docker operations.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import logging\n4: from pathlib import Path\n5: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n6: \n7: import docker\n8: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n9: \n10: \n11: class DockerService:\n12:     \"\"\"Service for Docker-related operations.\"\"\"\n13: \n14:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False):\n15:         self.verbose = verbose\n16:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n17:         if verbose:\n18:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n19:         else:\n20:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\n21: \n22:     @staticmethod\n23:     def generate_python_dockerfile(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n24:         \"\"\"\n25:         Generate Dockerfile content for Python agents.\n26: \n27:         Args:\n28:             metadata: AgentMetadata with agent configuration\n29: \n30:         Returns:\n31:             Dockerfile content as string\n32:         \"\"\"\n33:         lines = [\n34:             \"FROM python:3.11-slim\",\n35:             \"\",\n36:             \"WORKDIR /app\",\n37:             \"\",\n38:         ]\n39: \n40:         if metadata.requirements_file:\n41:             lines.append(f\"COPY {metadata.requirements_file} .\")\n42:             lines.append(f\"RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r {metadata.requirements_file}\")\n43:             lines.append(\"\")\n44: \n45:         lines.append(\"COPY . .\")\n46:         lines.append(\"\")\n47:         lines.append(f\"EXPOSE {metadata.port}\")\n48:         lines.append(\"\")\n49: \n50:         if metadata.entrypoint:\n51:             entrypoint_cmd = metadata.entrypoint\n52:         else:\n53:             entrypoint_cmd = \"python main.py\"\n54: \n55:         lines.append(f\"CMD {entrypoint_cmd}\")\n56: \n57:         return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n58: \n59:     @staticmethod\n60:     def generate_java_dockerfile(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n61:         \"\"\"\n62:         Generate Dockerfile content for Java agents.\n63: \n64:         Args:\n65:             metadata: AgentMetadata with agent configuration\n66: \n67:         Returns:\n68:             Dockerfile content as string\n69:         \"\"\"\n70:         lines = [\n71:             \"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\",\n72:             \"\",\n73:             \"WORKDIR /app\",\n74:             \"\",\n75:             \"COPY pom.xml .\",\n76:             \"RUN mvn dependency:go-offline -B\",\n77:             \"\",\n78:             \"COPY src ./src\",\n79:             \"RUN mvn package -DskipTests\",\n80:             \"\",\n81:             \"FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre\",\n82:             \"\",\n83:             \"WORKDIR /app\",\n84:             \"\",\n85:             \"COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\",\n86:             \"\",\n87:             f\"EXPOSE {metadata.port}\",\n88:             \"\",\n89:         ]\n90: \n91:         if metadata.entrypoint:\n92:             entrypoint_cmd = metadata.entrypoint\n93:         else:\n94:             entrypoint_cmd = \"java -jar app.jar\"\n95: \n96:         lines.append(f'CMD [\"{entrypoint_cmd}\"]')\n97: \n98:         return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n99: \n100:     @staticmethod\n101:     def write_dockerfile(workspace_path: Path, content: str) -> Path:\n102:         \"\"\"\n103:         Write Dockerfile content to workspace.\n104: \n105:         Args:\n106:             workspace_path: Path to workspace directory\n107:             content: Dockerfile content\n108: \n109:         Returns:\n110:             Path to the written Dockerfile\n111:         \"\"\"\n112:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n113: \n114:         with open(dockerfile_path, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n115:             f.write(content)\n116: \n117:         return dockerfile_path\n118: \n119:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n120:         \"\"\"\n121:         Check if Docker is available and running.\n122: \n123:         Returns:\n124:             True if Docker is available, False otherwise\n125:         \"\"\"\n126:         try:\n127:             client = docker.from_env()\n128:             client.ping()\n129:             self.logger.debug(\"Docker is available\")\n130:             return True\n131:         except docker.errors.DockerException:\n132:             self.logger.warning(\"Docker is not available\")\n133:             return False\n134: \n135:     def build_image(\n136:         self,\n137:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n138:         context_path: Path,\n139:         image_name: str,\n140:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n141:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n142:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n143:         \"\"\"\n144:         Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\n145: \n146:         Args:\n147:             dockerfile_path: Path to the Dockerfile\n148:             context_path: Build context path\n149:             image_name: Name for the image\n150:             tag: Tag for the image\n151:             build_args: Build arguments for docker build\n152: \n153:         Returns:\n154:             Dictionary with image info (image_id, tags)\n155:         \"\"\"\n156:         try:\n157:             client = docker.from_env()\n158:             image_tag = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n159: \n160:             self.logger.debug(f\"Building image: {image_tag}\")\n161: \n162:             build_output = client.images.build(\n163:                 path=str(context_path),\n164:                 dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n165:                 tag=image_tag,\n166:                 buildargs=build_args or {},\n167:                 rm=True,\n168:             )\n169: \n170:             image = build_output[0]\n171:             self.logger.debug(f\"Image built successfully: {image.id}\")\n172: \n173:             return {\n174:                 \"image_id\": image.id,\n175:                 \"tags\": [image_tag],\n176:             }\n177:         except docker.errors.BuildError as e:\n178:             self.logger.error(f\"Build failed: {e}\")\n179:             raise ValueError(f\"Docker build failed: {e}\")\n180:         except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n181:             self.logger.error(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n182:             raise ValueError(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n183: \n184:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n185:         \"\"\"\n186:         Get information about a Docker image.\n187: \n188:         Args:\n189:             image_name: Name of the image\n190: \n191:         Returns:\n192:             Dictionary with image info\n193:         \"\"\"\n194:         try:\n195:             client = docker.from_env()\n196:             image = client.images.get(image_name)\n197:             return {\n198:                 \"id\": image.id,\n199:                 \"tags\": image.tags,\n200:                 \"size\": str(image.attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)),\n201:             }\n202:         except docker.errors.NotFound:\n203:             raise ValueError(f\"Image not found: {image_name}\")\n204:         except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n205:             raise ValueError(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n206: \n207:     def push_image(\n208:         self,\n209:         image_name: str,\n210:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n211:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n212:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n213:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n214:         \"\"\"\n215:         Push a Docker image to a registry.\n216: \n217:         Args:\n218:             image_name: Name of the image to push\n219:             registry_url: Registry URL\n220:             username: Username for authentication\n221:             password: Password for authentication\n222: \n223:         Returns:\n224:             Dictionary with push status\n225:         \"\"\"\n226:         try:\n227:             client = docker.from_env()\n228: \n229:             if registry_url and username and password:\n230:                 client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry_url)\n231: \n232:             self.logger.debug(f\"Pushing image: {image_name}\")\n233:             image = client.images.get(image_name)\n234:             for line in image.push(stream=True, decode=True):\n235:                 if \"status\" in line:\n236:                     self.logger.debug(line[\"status\"])\n237: \n238:             return {\"status\": \"success\", \"image\": image_name}\n239:         except docker.errors.NotFound:\n240:             raise ValueError(f\"Image not found: {image_name}\")\n241:         except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n242:             raise ValueError(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n243: \n244:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n245:         \"\"\"\n246:         Remove a Docker image.\n247: \n248:         Args:\n249:             image_name: Name of the image to remove\n250: \n251:         Returns:\n252:             True if successful\n253:         \"\"\"\n254:         try:\n255:             client = docker.from_env()\n256:             client.images.remove(image_name)\n257:             self.logger.debug(f\"Image removed: {image_name}\")\n258:             return True\n259:         except docker.errors.NotFound:\n260:             raise ValueError(f\"Image not found: {image_name}\")\n261:         except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n262:             raise ValueError(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n\n(End of file - total 262 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Docker service for AgentCube - handles Dockerfile generation and Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nimport docker\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for Docker-related operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False):\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n        else:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/docker_service.py","time":{"start":1775865036406,"end":1775865036447}}}}
