{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865054270,"sessionID":"ses_2863226e8ffepDL9AgHZo0O2a1","part":{"id":"prt_d79ce3d2f001TCF1xAaFRm6dUV","messageID":"msg_d79ce2b01001B3Ik4XDw9RxPVt","sessionID":"ses_2863226e8ffepDL9AgHZo0O2a1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f5563cb0236b4f6690b6d7d0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n2: \n3: **AR:** AR-024  \n4: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n5: **Language:** Python  \n6: **Size:** M  \n7: \n8: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: DockerService Helper Methods\n13: - [ ] **T001** Implement `_format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str` method in DockerService (AR-024-006)\n14: - [ ] **T002** Implement `_get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` internal method with size formatting (AR-024-003-C)\n15: - [ ] **T003** Implement `_docker_login_sdk(registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str)` helper method (AR-024-007)\n16: - [ ] **T004** Implement `_tag_image_sdk(source_image: str, target_image: str)` helper method (AR-024-008)\n17: \n18: ### Phase 2: DockerService Return Value Updates\n19: - [ ] **T005** Update `build_image` return dict to include `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time` (AR-024-002)\n20: - [ ] **T006** Update `get_image_info` return dict to include `created` field (AR-024-003-A)\n21: - [ ] **T007** Update `push_image` return dict to include `pushed_image`, `push_time` (AR-024-004-A)\n22: - [ ] **T008** Update `push_image` to handle image retagging for registry URLs (AR-024-004-C)\n23: \n24: ### Phase 3: PackRuntime Integration\n25: - [ ] **T009** Add Docker availability check in PackRuntime before Dockerfile generation (AR-024-010-A)\n26: - [ ] **T010** Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if Docker unavailable in pack --build-mode local\n27: \n28: ### Phase 4: PublishRuntime Integration\n29: - [ ] **T011** Add DockerService to PublishRuntime (AR-024-010-C)\n30: - [ ] **T012** Implement `_prepare_local_image` method using `push_image` with registry credentials (AR-024-010-C)\n31: - [ ] **T013** Handle image retagging before pushing to registry\n32: \n33: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n34: - [ ] **T014** Add generic Exception catch as fallback in DockerService methods (AR-024-011-A)\n35: - [ ] **T015** Handle remove_image for non-existent image (return False, log warning) (AR-024-005-B)\n36: \n37: ### Phase 6: Verbose Logging\n38: - [ ] **T016** Ensure all DockerService methods log at debug level when verbose=True (AR-024-009)\n39: \n40: ### Phase 7: Testing\n41: - [ ] **T017** Write unit tests for `_format_size` (AR-024-006-A/B/C)\n42: - [ ] **T018** Write unit tests for `_docker_login_sdk` (AR-024-007-A/B)\n43: - [ ] **T019** Write unit tests for `_tag_image_sdk` (AR-024-008-A)\n44: - [ ] **T020** Write unit tests for `check_docker_available` (AR-024-001-A/B/C)\n45: - [ ] **T021** Write unit tests for `build_image` with build args (AR-024-002-C)\n46: - [ ] **T022** Write unit tests for `push_image` without auth (AR-024-004-A)\n47: - [ ] **T023** Write unit tests for `push_image` with auth (AR-024-004-B)\n48: - [ ] **T024** Write unit tests for `remove_image` (AR-024-005-A/B/C)\n49: - [ ] **T025** Write integration test for BuildRuntime using DockerService (AR-024-010-B)\n50: - [ ] **T026** Write integration test for PublishRuntime using DockerService (AR-024-010-C)\n51: \n52: ### Phase 8: Documentation\n53: - [ ] **T027** Update DockerService docstrings with return value descriptions\n54: - [ ] **T028** Document DockerService API in delta-spec\n55: \n56: ## Verification Criteria\n57: \n58: - [ ] **VC001** DockerService.check_docker_available() returns True when Docker running (mock test)\n59: - [ ] **VC002** DockerService.check_docker_available() returns False when Docker not running (mock test)\n60: - [ ] **VC003** DockerService._format_size() returns \"1.00 KB\" for 1024 bytes\n61: - [ ] **VC004** DockerService._format_size() returns \"10.00 MB\" for 10485760 bytes\n62: - [ ] **VC005** DockerService._format_size() returns \"1.00 GB\" for 1073741824 bytes\n63: - [ ] **VC006** DockerService.build_image() returns dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time\n64: - [ ] **VC007** DockerService.push_image() returns dict with pushed_image, push_time\n65: - [ ] **VC008** DockerService.remove_image() returns True for existing image, False for non-existent\n66: - [ ] **VC009** PackRuntime raises error when Docker unavailable in local build mode\n67: - [ ] **VC010** All unit tests pass\n68: - [ ] **VC011** All integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 68 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n\n**AR:** AR-024  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: DockerService Helper Methods\n- [ ] **T001** Implement `_format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str` method in DockerService (AR-024-006)\n- [ ] **T002** Implement `_get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` internal method with size formatting (AR-024-003-C)\n- [ ] **T003** Implement `_docker_login_sdk(registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str)` helper method (AR-024-007)\n- [ ] **T004** Implement `_tag_image_sdk(source_image: str, target_image: str)` helper method (AR-024-008)\n\n### Phase 2: DockerService Return Value Updates\n- [ ] **T005** Update `build_image` return dict to include `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time` (AR-024-002)\n- [ ] **T006** Update `get_image_info` return dict to include `created` field (AR-024-003-A)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"